The paper discusses the deployment of artificial intelligence using deep learning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus of the paper is on memory-augmented neural networks (MANNs), which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the implementation of MANNs on mobile devices, which involves hardware optimization and falls under the category of cs.ET (Embedded Systems). The paper proposes a novel approach called inference thresholding, which is related to natural language processing (NLP) tasks and falls under the category of cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
